WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:20.760
The Wind in the Willows by Kenneth Graham

00:20.760 --> 00:25.840
Chapter 1 The Riverbank

00:25.840 --> 00:30.560
It is spring and the mould is cleaning his little home.

00:30.560 --> 00:35.400
He is working very hard and he is very tired.

00:35.400 --> 00:38.880
Suddenly he decides to stop.

00:38.880 --> 00:41.720
He wants to go outside.

00:41.720 --> 00:46.880
He goes up a small tunnel and arrives outside in a meadow.

00:46.880 --> 00:50.800
This is nice.

00:50.800 --> 00:54.680
He thinks when he arrives in the sunlight.

00:54.680 --> 00:57.560
This is better than cleaning.

00:57.560 --> 00:59.920
He is very happy.

00:59.920 --> 01:02.800
He crosses meadows and woods.

01:02.800 --> 01:07.560
He sees rabbits, birds and a lot of other animals.

01:07.560 --> 01:10.720
They are all working hard.

01:10.720 --> 01:13.840
Finally he arrives at the river.

01:13.840 --> 01:17.320
He sits down on the grass.

01:17.320 --> 01:20.880
The water rad comes out of his hole in the riverbank.

01:20.880 --> 01:22.760
He sees mole.

01:22.760 --> 01:23.760
Hello, Mole.

01:23.760 --> 01:24.760
He says.

01:24.760 --> 01:26.080
Would you like to come over?

01:26.080 --> 01:27.680
Oh, hello, Rad.

01:27.680 --> 01:29.280
Yes, I would.

01:29.280 --> 01:30.280
But how?

01:30.280 --> 01:31.280
Replies mole.

01:31.280 --> 01:34.520
I can come and get you in my boat.

01:34.520 --> 01:38.960
Rad gets into a little boat and crosses the river.

01:38.960 --> 01:42.080
Mole gets into the boat.

01:42.080 --> 01:44.440
This is wonderful.

01:44.440 --> 01:45.920
Says mole.

01:45.920 --> 01:49.240
This is my first time in a boat.

01:49.240 --> 01:52.160
Your first time says Rad.

01:52.160 --> 01:54.080
There's nothing better than boats.

01:54.080 --> 01:55.680
Let's go for a picnic.

01:55.680 --> 01:58.800
Oh, yes, please.

01:58.800 --> 02:00.880
Says mole.

02:00.880 --> 02:06.880
Rad goes into his house and returns with a big basket full of food.

02:06.880 --> 02:10.480
They go down the river in the boat.

02:10.480 --> 02:17.040
Rad tells Mole about life on the river and about his neighbours, the otters, kingfishers

02:17.040 --> 02:19.840
and moorhens.

02:19.840 --> 02:22.440
Mole sees a wood in the distance.

02:22.440 --> 02:24.800
What's over there?

02:24.800 --> 02:25.800
He asks.

02:25.800 --> 02:29.480
That's the wild wood, says Rad.

02:29.480 --> 02:31.080
We don't go there often.

02:31.080 --> 02:33.920
Are they nice people there?

02:33.920 --> 02:34.920
asks Mole.

02:34.920 --> 02:37.640
Well, replies Rad.

02:37.640 --> 02:40.040
The squirrels and rabbits are all right.

02:40.040 --> 02:41.040
And there's Badger.

02:41.040 --> 02:42.560
He's nice.

02:42.560 --> 02:49.000
But the weasels, stoats and foxes, you must be careful with them.

02:49.000 --> 02:53.920
They stop for their picnic and Mole unpacks the basket.

02:53.920 --> 02:55.920
Soon the otter arrives.

02:55.920 --> 02:59.080
Hello, Otter, says Rad.

02:59.080 --> 03:01.080
This is my friend Mr. Mole.

03:01.080 --> 03:02.640
Please, to meet you.

03:02.640 --> 03:05.280
Says Otter to Mole.

03:05.280 --> 03:11.240
Suddenly the Badger appears and Rad invites him to the picnic.

03:11.240 --> 03:14.560
But Badger turns around and goes away.

03:14.560 --> 03:18.120
Badger hates company, says Rad.

03:18.120 --> 03:19.960
We don't see him often.

03:19.960 --> 03:23.400
But look, there's toad on the river in his new boat.

03:23.400 --> 03:25.400
He's toad's new hobby.

03:25.400 --> 03:26.400
Says Otter.

03:26.400 --> 03:29.200
Yes, says Rad.

03:29.200 --> 03:32.480
First it was sailing, then it was house boating.

03:32.480 --> 03:35.960
He changes hobby all the time.

03:35.960 --> 03:40.400
Rad waves to toad, but toad doesn't stop.

03:40.400 --> 03:44.080
Rad and Mole return to Rad's house in the boat.

03:44.080 --> 03:46.760
Rad invites Mole to stay with him.

03:46.760 --> 03:59.520
And Mole is very happy.

03:59.520 --> 04:07.360
Chapter 2 The Open Road

04:07.360 --> 04:12.960
One summer morning, Mole and Rad decide to visit Mr. Toad.

04:12.960 --> 04:16.160
They get in the boat and go up the river.

04:16.160 --> 04:19.240
Toad's rich, you know, says Rad.

04:19.240 --> 04:23.240
Is toad very nice, asks Mole.

04:23.240 --> 04:25.960
Oh yes, replies Rad.

04:25.960 --> 04:27.600
He's very nice.

04:27.600 --> 04:31.880
He isn't very intelligent, but we can't all be clever.

04:31.880 --> 04:35.160
And sometimes he's boastful and arrogant.

04:35.160 --> 04:38.480
But he's got some good qualities.

04:38.480 --> 04:41.960
Soon they arrive at Toad Hall.

04:41.960 --> 04:44.360
They pass by a boating house.

04:44.440 --> 04:47.080
It is full of boats.

04:47.080 --> 04:49.880
They are all out of the water.

04:49.880 --> 04:53.520
It seems that Toad isn't interested in boating anymore.

04:53.520 --> 04:57.960
I wonder what his new hobby is, says Rad.

04:57.960 --> 05:04.120
Rad and Mole get out of the boat and walk across the gardens of Toad Hall.

05:04.120 --> 05:06.920
They see Toad in the garden.

05:06.920 --> 05:09.880
He is looking at a big map.

05:09.880 --> 05:13.680
He is very pleased to see Rad and Mole.

05:13.680 --> 05:16.040
Hello Toad, says Rad.

05:16.040 --> 05:17.760
This is my friend Mole.

05:17.760 --> 05:20.720
Oh splendid, Christ Toad.

05:20.720 --> 05:25.320
Please, to meet you, come and see my new hobby.

05:25.320 --> 05:28.480
He shows them a gypsy caravan.

05:28.480 --> 05:32.000
It is yellow and green with red wheels.

05:32.000 --> 05:35.800
There's real life, Christ Toad.

05:35.800 --> 05:42.680
The open road, travel, change, interest, excitement.

05:42.680 --> 05:45.840
Look inside, everything's there.

05:45.840 --> 05:49.320
We've got everything for our journey this afternoon.

05:49.320 --> 05:55.320
Excuse me, you say, we, our, this afternoon?

05:55.320 --> 05:56.880
Ask Rad.

05:56.880 --> 06:01.120
Yes, ready, I can't go without you, says Toad.

06:01.120 --> 06:05.480
Oh Rad, it's so exciting, says Mole.

06:05.480 --> 06:07.480
Very well, says Rad.

06:07.480 --> 06:09.160
Let's go.

06:09.160 --> 06:14.280
After lunch, they go to the paddock and catch the old grey horse.

06:14.280 --> 06:17.160
Then they set off on the road.

06:17.160 --> 06:22.320
It is a lovely afternoon and the birds whistle at them.

06:22.320 --> 06:27.440
And passers by say, good afternoon.

06:27.440 --> 06:31.760
In the evening, they stop and eat a simple meal.

06:31.760 --> 06:34.280
Then they go to bed.

06:34.280 --> 06:40.840
The next morning, Toad sleeps until very late, so Mole walks to the nearest village.

06:40.840 --> 06:46.600
He buys milk and eggs for breakfast and rat lights a fire and washes the dinner plates

06:46.600 --> 06:48.840
from the night before.

06:48.840 --> 06:52.360
They are very tired after this hard work.

06:52.360 --> 06:55.760
Finally, Toad gets up.

06:55.760 --> 07:02.040
Ugh, life on the road is very easy, he says.

07:02.040 --> 07:04.760
In a breakfast, they set off.

07:04.760 --> 07:13.400
They are walking along the road when suddenly a magnificent motor car drives past.

07:13.400 --> 07:23.920
The horse is frightened and pulls the caravan off the road into a ditch.

07:23.920 --> 07:28.840
The caravan is ruined, rat is furious.

07:28.840 --> 07:31.880
You villains, police help!

07:31.880 --> 07:36.960
He shouts, but Toad is sitting in the middle of the road.

07:36.960 --> 07:40.200
He is staring in the direction of the motor car.

07:40.200 --> 07:41.400
Poop, poop!

07:41.400 --> 07:44.760
He says, poop, poop!

07:44.760 --> 07:50.160
Rat and Mole try to pull the caravan out of the ditch, but they can't.

07:50.160 --> 07:53.840
Rat asks, can you help us Toad?

07:53.840 --> 07:55.440
Poop, poop!

07:55.440 --> 07:57.720
replies Toad.

07:57.720 --> 08:03.640
Now that's the real way to travel, the only way.

08:03.640 --> 08:08.840
The caravan is ruined and they must return home by train.

08:08.840 --> 08:24.920
The next day Toad buys a big and very expensive motor car.

08:24.920 --> 08:39.360
Number three, the Wildwood.

08:39.360 --> 08:42.720
Mole wants to meet Badger.

08:42.720 --> 08:44.800
Could you ask him here for dinner?

08:44.800 --> 08:46.440
He asks Rat.

08:46.440 --> 08:47.880
He wouldn't come.

08:47.880 --> 08:49.240
replies Rat.

08:49.240 --> 08:50.640
He hates company.

08:50.640 --> 08:53.680
Well, can we go and call on him?

08:53.680 --> 08:55.200
It suggests Mole.

08:55.200 --> 08:57.440
Oh no, says Rat.

08:57.440 --> 08:59.600
He's very shy.

08:59.600 --> 09:03.400
And also, he lives in the middle of the Wildwood.

09:03.400 --> 09:08.240
It is clear that Rat doesn't want to visit Badger.

09:08.240 --> 09:12.760
It is winter time, and Rat sleeps a lot.

09:12.760 --> 09:17.680
One afternoon, he is sleeping in his armchair in front of the fire.

09:17.680 --> 09:23.560
So Mole decides to go and explore the Wildwood and meet Badger.

09:23.560 --> 09:25.960
He goes outside.

09:25.960 --> 09:30.440
It is very cold, and the sky is gray.

09:30.440 --> 09:32.000
He is happy.

09:32.000 --> 09:37.440
And when he arrives at the Wildwood, he is not frightened.

09:37.440 --> 09:46.640
Then he starts to see faces, hundreds of faces, little faces with hard eyes.

09:46.640 --> 09:50.400
Mole is frightened and leaves the path.

09:50.400 --> 09:52.880
In a panic, Mole starts to run.

09:52.880 --> 09:54.840
He doesn't know where.

09:54.840 --> 10:00.360
Finally, he hides inside the hollow of an old tree.

10:00.360 --> 10:03.720
Rat wakes up and looks for Mole.

10:03.720 --> 10:06.760
But Mole is not there.

10:06.760 --> 10:09.880
Mole's hat and boots are gone.

10:09.880 --> 10:12.880
Rat goes outside and sees footprints.

10:12.880 --> 10:16.760
They are going in the direction of the Wildwood.

10:16.760 --> 10:18.960
Rat is worried.

10:18.960 --> 10:27.600
He goes back into the house, takes two pistols, and a big stick, and sets off for the Wildwood.

10:27.600 --> 10:31.200
He also sees little faces with hard eyes.

10:31.200 --> 10:35.680
But they disappear immediately when they see his pistols and stick.

10:35.680 --> 10:38.840
Rat hunts for an hour.

10:38.840 --> 10:41.960
Mole, Mole, where are you?

10:41.960 --> 10:44.560
It's me, Rat.

10:44.560 --> 10:47.960
Finally, he hears a cry.

10:48.320 --> 10:50.800
Ratty, is that really you?

10:50.800 --> 10:53.600
I'm so frightened.

10:53.600 --> 10:56.800
Rat sees Mole under the tree.

10:56.800 --> 11:00.720
Mole, you mustn't come into the Wildwood alone.

11:00.720 --> 11:04.520
We animals from the riverbank always come in couples.

11:04.520 --> 11:10.240
But brave Mr. Toad isn't frightened of the wood, says Mole.

11:10.240 --> 11:11.240
Rat laughs.

11:11.240 --> 11:12.240
Toad?

11:12.240 --> 11:17.240
He wouldn't come here for a hatful of gold.

11:17.320 --> 11:21.120
Now we must leave her home before night comes.

11:21.120 --> 11:23.400
Rat looks around.

11:23.400 --> 11:29.160
It's snowing, and everything looks so different in the snow.

11:29.160 --> 11:35.160
They set off bravely, but after two hours they stop for a rest.

11:35.160 --> 11:39.680
The snow is very deep, and they are very tired and wet.

11:39.680 --> 11:43.120
We're very tired, says Rat.

11:43.120 --> 11:46.080
Let's find a dry cave or hole.

11:46.080 --> 11:50.320
Then we can rest before trying again.

11:50.320 --> 11:52.080
They look for shelter.

11:52.080 --> 11:55.080
Suddenly, Mole falls down.

11:55.080 --> 11:58.200
Oh, oh, my leg.

11:58.200 --> 11:59.480
He cries.

11:59.480 --> 12:02.800
Poor Mole, says Rat.

12:02.800 --> 12:05.600
He looks at the cut on Mole's leg.

12:05.600 --> 12:10.080
This is a cut from metal, not a branch, he says.

12:10.080 --> 12:13.120
He starts to dig in the snow.

12:13.120 --> 12:15.120
Hooray, hooray.

12:15.120 --> 12:16.120
He shouts.

12:16.120 --> 12:17.720
What is it?

12:17.720 --> 12:19.840
asks Mole.

12:19.840 --> 12:23.000
They see a little green door.

12:23.000 --> 12:26.480
A bell is hanging next to it.

12:26.480 --> 12:31.600
Under the bell is written, Mr. Badger.

12:31.600 --> 12:36.080
Rat hits the door with his stick, and Mole rings the bell.

12:45.120 --> 12:52.800
Animals in Winter.

12:52.800 --> 13:00.200
In wintertime it gets cold, snow covers the ground, and there is no food.

13:00.200 --> 13:04.680
So how do animals survive?

13:04.680 --> 13:06.800
Migration.

13:06.800 --> 13:12.320
Many birds, fish and other animals migrate in the autumn.

13:12.320 --> 13:18.920
They travel south to warmer places and then return in the spring.

13:18.920 --> 13:21.240
Adaptation.

13:21.240 --> 13:27.440
Some animals, like the Mole, stay and remain active in the winter months.

13:27.440 --> 13:33.120
To keep warm they may grow new thicker fur in autumn.

13:33.120 --> 13:39.640
Because food is difficult to find, some animals like mice and squirrels collect extra food

13:39.640 --> 13:43.800
and store it to eat later.

13:43.800 --> 13:45.880
Hibernation.

13:45.880 --> 13:51.320
Some animals, such as the rat, hibernate during the winter.

13:51.320 --> 13:55.520
This is a special, very deep sleep.

13:55.520 --> 14:01.880
The animal's body temperature goes down, and its heartbeat and breathing slow down.

14:01.880 --> 14:08.320
In the autumn, these animals prepare by eating extra food, which is stored as body fat, and

14:08.320 --> 14:23.080
can be used as energy during the winter.

14:23.080 --> 14:34.000
Chapter 4 Mr. Badger.

14:34.000 --> 14:37.120
Mole and Rat wait for a long time.

14:37.120 --> 14:40.280
And finally they hear footsteps.

14:40.280 --> 14:46.280
The door opens a little, and they see a nose and two sleepy eyes.

14:46.280 --> 14:49.080
Who is it?

14:49.080 --> 14:50.080
Asks Badger.

14:50.080 --> 14:52.080
He is angry.

14:52.080 --> 14:54.080
Oh, Badger.

14:54.080 --> 14:55.080
Cries Rat.

14:55.080 --> 14:58.560
It's me, Rat, and my friend Mole.

14:58.560 --> 15:00.880
We're lost in the snow.

15:00.880 --> 15:04.280
My dear Ratty says Badger.

15:04.360 --> 15:09.600
Come in, lost in the snow, in the wild wood.

15:09.600 --> 15:14.440
This isn't the kind of night for small animals to be out.

15:14.440 --> 15:17.000
He takes them to the kitchen.

15:17.000 --> 15:20.280
There is a fire burning in the fireplace.

15:20.280 --> 15:23.880
Badger gives them dressing gowns and slippers.

15:23.880 --> 15:28.640
They sit in front of the fire, while Badger prepares dinner for them.

15:28.640 --> 15:33.360
They are very hungry, and they eat and eat.

15:33.360 --> 15:36.160
How's old told?

15:36.160 --> 15:37.160
Asks Badger.

15:37.160 --> 15:41.320
From bad to worse, says Rat.

15:41.320 --> 15:43.600
Another accident in his car.

15:43.600 --> 15:45.120
This is the seventh.

15:45.120 --> 15:48.240
He's always in hospital or paying fines.

15:48.240 --> 15:53.320
He needs to pay for a driver, but he's convinced that he's a good driver.

15:53.320 --> 15:54.320
Badger thinks.

15:54.320 --> 16:01.720
I can't do anything now, but when the nights are short, we must talk to Toad.

16:01.720 --> 16:03.840
He must become sensible.

16:03.840 --> 16:07.680
Now it's time for bed.

16:07.680 --> 16:10.160
He takes them to a room.

16:10.160 --> 16:17.200
It is full of food for the winter, apples, turnips, potatoes, nuts, and honey.

16:17.200 --> 16:20.880
But there are also two little beds.

16:20.880 --> 16:26.400
Mole and Rat get undressed and go to sleep.

16:26.400 --> 16:30.320
The next morning they get up very late.

16:30.320 --> 16:34.880
They are eating breakfast in the kitchen when the front doorbell rings.

16:34.880 --> 16:36.960
It's Otter.

16:36.960 --> 16:40.040
He is very happy to see Rat and Mole.

16:40.040 --> 16:46.000
Everybody on the river is very worried about you, he says.

16:46.000 --> 16:48.520
At that moment, Badger arrives.

16:48.520 --> 16:54.040
I think it's time for lunch, he says.

16:54.040 --> 16:58.480
During lunch, Otter and Rat talk about the river.

16:58.480 --> 17:04.280
Mole tells Badger, I like your house, it's good to live underground.

17:04.280 --> 17:07.560
Badger is pleased that Mole likes his house.

17:07.560 --> 17:13.800
Yes, here it's safe, peaceful, and quiet.

17:13.800 --> 17:18.080
After lunch, Badger shows Mole his home.

17:18.080 --> 17:21.280
There are a lot of rooms and tunnels.

17:21.280 --> 17:23.480
They return to the kitchen.

17:23.480 --> 17:25.560
Ratty is wearing his coat.

17:25.920 --> 17:29.120
Come on Mole, it's time to go, he says.

17:29.120 --> 17:31.600
We must go before night.

17:31.600 --> 17:32.920
He is worried.

17:32.920 --> 17:35.560
It's all right, says Otter.

17:35.560 --> 17:37.480
I'm coming with you.

17:37.480 --> 17:39.840
Don't worry Ratty.

17:39.840 --> 17:41.080
Says Badger.

17:41.080 --> 17:45.200
My tunnels go to the edge of the wood.

17:45.200 --> 17:50.520
He picks up a lantern and takes them down a long tunnel.

17:50.520 --> 17:54.280
After a long time, they see daylight.

17:54.320 --> 17:58.440
They are on the edge of the wild wood.

17:58.440 --> 18:03.080
Badger says goodbye and goes away quickly.

18:03.080 --> 18:06.320
Otter takes them to the river.

18:06.320 --> 18:09.200
Mole is very happy to be home.

18:09.200 --> 18:28.640
Chapter 5, Mr. Toad.

18:28.640 --> 18:32.000
It is a sunny morning in summer.

18:32.000 --> 18:34.800
Mole and Rat are having breakfast.

18:34.800 --> 18:39.560
Suddenly there is a knock at the door.

18:39.560 --> 18:43.720
Mole goes to the door and comes back with Badger.

18:43.720 --> 18:46.360
Badger looks very serious.

18:46.360 --> 18:47.680
It's time.

18:47.680 --> 18:50.120
He says, time for what?

18:50.120 --> 18:51.800
Asks Rat.

18:51.800 --> 18:53.520
He looks at the clock.

18:53.520 --> 18:54.880
Time for who?

18:54.880 --> 18:56.440
Says Badger.

18:56.440 --> 18:58.440
Time for Toad.

18:58.440 --> 19:00.440
We must talk to him.

19:00.440 --> 19:05.880
I know that another big new motor car is arriving at Toad Hall today.

19:05.880 --> 19:10.360
We must go and talk to Toad before it's too late.

19:10.360 --> 19:12.360
Good, says Rat.

19:12.360 --> 19:15.360
We must save poor Toad.

19:15.360 --> 19:21.840
When they arrive at Toad Hall, a big red car is in front of the house.

19:21.840 --> 19:24.600
Toad is coming out of the house.

19:24.600 --> 19:30.320
He is wearing goggles, a cap, an enormous coat, and gloves.

19:30.320 --> 19:34.400
Hello, he says when he sees them.

19:34.400 --> 19:39.760
Take him inside, says Badger to Rat and Mole.

19:39.760 --> 19:41.960
They take him inside.

19:41.960 --> 19:47.320
Now Toad, says Badger, take these stupid clothes off.

19:47.320 --> 19:49.360
No, says Toad.

19:49.360 --> 19:51.320
Why are you doing this?

19:51.320 --> 19:54.560
Take his clothes off, Badger orders.

19:54.560 --> 19:59.760
Rat sits on Toad and Mole takes off Toad's motor clothes.

19:59.760 --> 20:10.840
Now, Toad, says Badger, you don't listen to our advice, you're spending all your money

20:10.840 --> 20:16.840
and people are talking about the animals because of your fast driving and problems with the

20:16.840 --> 20:17.840
police.

20:17.840 --> 20:20.920
But Toad is not sorry.

20:20.920 --> 20:23.360
So they lock him in a bedroom.

20:23.360 --> 20:28.120
You can come out when you're sorry, says Rat.

20:28.120 --> 20:30.080
They go downstairs.

20:30.080 --> 20:33.480
Toad shouts at them through the keyhole.

20:33.480 --> 20:36.920
Toad's very determined, says Badger.

20:36.920 --> 20:39.520
It's a difficult situation.

20:39.520 --> 20:44.400
We must never leave Toad alone.

20:44.400 --> 20:49.600
The days pass, but Toad is still interested in cars.

20:49.600 --> 20:52.800
He becomes depressed.

20:52.800 --> 20:56.000
Good morning, Rat is with Toad.

20:56.000 --> 20:57.800
How are you today, Toad?

20:57.800 --> 20:59.200
He asks.

20:59.200 --> 21:01.360
Not very well.

21:01.360 --> 21:03.240
replies Toad.

21:03.240 --> 21:07.680
Could you go to the village and call the doctor?

21:07.680 --> 21:09.240
Rat is worried.

21:09.240 --> 21:11.040
A doctor?

21:11.040 --> 21:14.240
He must be very ill.

21:14.240 --> 21:17.880
He goes out of the room and locks the door.

21:17.880 --> 21:21.360
Then he runs to the village.

21:21.360 --> 21:24.080
And jumps out of bed and laughs.

21:24.080 --> 21:26.440
He gets dressed quickly.

21:26.440 --> 21:28.840
He puts some money in his pockets.

21:28.840 --> 21:33.080
He climbs out of the window and jumps to the ground.

21:33.080 --> 21:38.280
He then walks away in the opposite direction to Rat.

21:38.280 --> 21:43.880
The sun is shining and he is very happy with himself.

21:43.880 --> 21:46.760
Poor Ratty, he thinks.

21:46.760 --> 21:50.120
He's a very good animal, but not very intelligent.

21:50.120 --> 21:52.920
I must educate him one day.

21:52.920 --> 21:57.160
He arrives in a small town and sees a sign.

21:57.160 --> 21:59.400
The red lion.

21:59.400 --> 22:01.560
Toad is very hungry.

22:01.560 --> 22:06.560
He goes into the inn and orders a big lunch.

22:06.560 --> 22:13.120
Suddenly he hears, and sees a car outside the inn.

22:13.120 --> 22:17.040
The people get out and go into the inn.

22:17.040 --> 22:19.400
Toad walks outside.

22:19.400 --> 22:21.760
He looks at the car.

22:21.760 --> 22:29.600
I wonder, he thinks, if this type of car starts easily.

22:29.600 --> 22:37.640
In a dream, he starts the car.

22:37.640 --> 22:46.840
Then sits in the driver's seat and drives away.

22:46.840 --> 22:49.560
He doesn't think about right or wrong.

22:49.560 --> 22:58.160
He drives faster and faster.

22:58.160 --> 23:02.920
We must punish this villain severely, says the magistrate.

23:02.920 --> 23:08.920
His guilty, first of all, of stealing a motor car, and secondly, of driving dangerously,

23:08.920 --> 23:12.920
and thirdly of being rude to the police.

23:12.920 --> 23:17.680
I give you twenty years in prison.

23:17.680 --> 23:37.480
Poor Toad is locked up in prison.

23:37.480 --> 23:50.680
Chapter 6 Toad's Adventures

23:50.680 --> 23:53.680
Toad is very unhappy.

23:53.680 --> 23:59.400
Oh, this is the end of everything.

23:59.400 --> 24:00.400
He thinks.

24:00.400 --> 24:04.320
The end of the career of Toad.

24:04.320 --> 24:15.040
The popular and handsome Toad, the rich and kind Toad, he starts crying.

24:15.040 --> 24:28.240
Now I must stay in this dark prison, a clever rat and sensible mole, intelligent badger.

24:28.240 --> 24:30.520
Poor Toad.

24:30.520 --> 24:36.320
The days and weeks pass, and he refuses to eat.

24:36.320 --> 24:42.320
The jailer has got a daughter, and she helps her father in the prison.

24:42.320 --> 24:48.280
She is very fond of animals, and is sorry for Toad.

24:48.280 --> 24:56.920
One day she asks, Father, please let me look after Toad, he's so unhappy and so thin.

24:56.920 --> 25:00.280
She knocks on the door of Toad's cell.

25:00.280 --> 25:10.240
Now, Toad, she says, sit up and stop crying, be sensible and eat some dinner.

25:10.240 --> 25:17.400
The dinner smells very good, and Toad starts to think that life is not so bad.

25:17.400 --> 25:21.120
He sits up and starts to eat.

25:21.120 --> 25:25.240
The jailer's daughter asks him about Toad Hall.

25:25.240 --> 25:28.680
He talks about his home.

25:28.680 --> 25:32.640
Then she asks him about his animal friends.

25:32.640 --> 25:41.440
When the girl leaves, Toad is himself again, the same, arrogant animal.

25:41.440 --> 25:46.800
The days pass, and they have a lot of interesting talks together.

25:46.800 --> 25:53.800
The jailer's daughter is very sorry for Toad, and thinks it is wrong that Toad is in prison.

25:53.880 --> 26:00.320
Toad believes that she is in love with him, and is a little sorry that the social gap

26:00.320 --> 26:03.960
between them is so big.

26:03.960 --> 26:08.760
One morning she says, listen Toad, I've got an aunt.

26:08.760 --> 26:12.800
She's a washer woman and does the washing for all the prisoners here.

26:12.800 --> 26:17.520
Now, you're very rich, and she's very poor.

26:17.520 --> 26:24.080
I think that if you pay her, she can give you her dress and bonnet, and you can escape.

26:24.080 --> 26:25.880
You are very similar.

26:25.880 --> 26:28.880
We are not, says Toad.

26:28.880 --> 26:32.360
I'm very elegant, considering I'm a Toad.

26:32.360 --> 26:35.840
My aunt's also elegant, considering she's a washer woman.

26:35.840 --> 26:36.840
Says the girl.

26:36.840 --> 26:42.200
I'm trying to help you, and you are proud and ungrateful.

26:42.200 --> 26:46.760
Please introduce me to your aunt, says Toad.

26:46.760 --> 26:51.520
The next evening, the girl's aunt comes into the cell.

26:51.520 --> 26:54.680
She is carrying Toad's washing.

26:54.680 --> 26:59.200
On the table is a pile of gold coins.

26:59.200 --> 27:05.480
The washer woman gives Toad a cotton dress, an apron, and a bonnet.

27:05.480 --> 27:11.680
Then Toad takes off his coat and waistcoat, and puts on the dress apron and bonnet.

27:11.680 --> 27:13.720
Goodbye, Toad!

27:13.720 --> 27:15.800
Says the girl.

27:15.800 --> 27:19.880
Toad is nervous, but he goes out.

27:19.880 --> 27:22.600
No one stops him.

27:22.600 --> 27:26.920
When he is outside, he walks towards the town.

27:26.920 --> 27:35.400
Soon he sees some red and green lights, and the noise of a train.

27:35.400 --> 27:37.000
Ah-ha!

27:37.000 --> 27:43.320
He thinks a railway station, I can catch a train home.

27:43.320 --> 27:49.440
He goes to the ticket office and asks for a ticket to the village near Toad Hall.

27:49.440 --> 27:51.880
But he has no money.

27:51.880 --> 27:55.840
It is all in his waistcoat pocket, in the prison.

27:55.840 --> 27:59.280
He cannot get home.

27:59.280 --> 28:01.560
Toad is very sad.

28:01.560 --> 28:04.480
He walks down the platform.

28:04.480 --> 28:06.480
He starts to cry.

28:06.480 --> 28:07.480
Hello!

28:07.480 --> 28:10.840
Watch the matter!

28:10.920 --> 28:13.240
He walks the train driver.

28:13.240 --> 28:14.240
Sir!

28:14.240 --> 28:15.240
Cries Toad.

28:15.240 --> 28:18.200
I am a poor, oh washer woman.

28:18.200 --> 28:19.680
I have no money.

28:19.680 --> 28:24.680
I can't pay for the ticket, and I must get home tonight.

28:24.680 --> 28:25.880
Very well.

28:25.880 --> 28:28.080
Says the kind train driver.

28:28.080 --> 28:29.760
You are the washer woman.

28:29.760 --> 28:34.320
I can give you a ride if you wash some shirts for me.

28:34.320 --> 28:36.200
Toad climbs up.

28:36.200 --> 28:41.840
The guard waves his flag, and the train moves out of the station.

28:41.840 --> 28:44.960
Now Toad is very happy.

28:44.960 --> 28:52.000
He thinks about Toad Hall, his friends, and good things to eat.

28:52.000 --> 28:54.600
After some time, the train driver says,

28:54.600 --> 28:59.400
It's very strange, we're the last train tonight, but I'm sure there's another train

28:59.400 --> 29:01.080
behind us.

29:01.080 --> 29:05.360
Toad immediately becomes serious and depressed.

29:05.360 --> 29:08.640
The train is full of policemen with truncheons.

29:08.640 --> 29:12.080
They're shouting, stop, stop, stop.

29:12.080 --> 29:15.640
Continues the train driver.

29:15.640 --> 29:18.720
Toad falls to his knees.

29:18.720 --> 29:20.720
Save me, Mr. Train Driver.

29:20.720 --> 29:22.320
I'm not a washer woman.

29:22.320 --> 29:23.320
I'm toad.

29:23.320 --> 29:27.800
The well-known and popular, Mr. Toad.

29:27.800 --> 29:28.800
They want me.

29:28.800 --> 29:32.200
I'm a car thief, and I'm running away from prison.

29:32.200 --> 29:35.640
The train driver looks very serious.

29:35.640 --> 29:41.040
I must stop and give you to the police, but you're obviously very sorry.

29:41.040 --> 29:43.120
Soon, there's a tunnel.

29:43.120 --> 29:45.160
At the other end, there's a wood.

29:45.160 --> 29:48.880
You must jump out and hide in the wood.

29:48.880 --> 29:51.800
After the tunnel, Toad jumps.

29:51.800 --> 29:54.760
He runs into the wood and hides.

29:54.760 --> 30:01.400
The police train comes out of the tunnel and continues following the other train.

30:01.400 --> 30:06.640
Toad laughs, but soon he stops laughing.

30:06.640 --> 30:11.240
It is very late and dark and cold.

30:11.240 --> 30:17.440
He is in a strange wood with no money and far away from friends and home.

30:17.440 --> 30:24.400
Cold, hungry and tired, he makes a bed with dead leaves and branches under a tree and

30:24.400 --> 30:25.560
goes to sleep.

30:31.400 --> 30:49.000
Chapter 7 The Further Adventures of Toad

30:49.000 --> 30:51.160
Toad wakes up early.

30:51.160 --> 30:54.480
The sun is shining.

30:54.480 --> 30:58.480
He stands up and starts walking.

30:58.480 --> 31:01.320
Soon he sees a canal.

31:01.320 --> 31:05.040
On it, there is a barge pulled by a horse.

31:05.040 --> 31:07.120
There is a woman on the barge.

31:07.120 --> 31:08.560
Good morning.

31:08.560 --> 31:12.840
She says to Toad, maybe it's good for you.

31:12.840 --> 31:20.200
Says Toad, but I am a poor water woman and I'm going to see my married daughter.

31:20.200 --> 31:21.680
She's in trouble.

31:21.680 --> 31:24.480
All my other children are alone.

31:24.480 --> 31:26.840
I'm lost with no money.

31:26.840 --> 31:29.120
Oh, where does your daughter live?

31:29.120 --> 31:31.120
Says Toad asks the barge woman.

31:31.120 --> 31:33.280
Near the river replies Toad.

31:33.280 --> 31:37.520
Near a fine house called Toad Hall.

31:37.520 --> 31:38.520
Toad Hall?

31:38.520 --> 31:40.640
I'm going in that direction.

31:40.640 --> 31:42.040
Says the woman.

31:42.040 --> 31:43.400
Come with me in the barge.

31:43.400 --> 31:46.160
I can take you near Toad Hall.

31:46.160 --> 31:48.800
Lucky Toad gets onto the barge.

31:48.800 --> 31:52.000
So, you're a washer woman.

31:52.000 --> 31:53.000
Asks the woman.

31:53.000 --> 31:54.000
Oh, yes.

31:54.000 --> 31:55.000
Says Toad.

31:55.000 --> 31:57.840
The best in the country and very good.

31:57.840 --> 31:59.400
I love washing.

31:59.400 --> 32:02.800
Oh, then I'm very lucky meeting you.

32:02.800 --> 32:03.800
Says the woman.

32:03.800 --> 32:07.680
I like washing too, but I never have the time.

32:07.680 --> 32:11.080
There's a big pile of washing inside.

32:11.080 --> 32:13.680
You can do my washing.

32:13.680 --> 32:14.680
Toad is frightened.

32:14.680 --> 32:15.680
Oh, no.

32:15.680 --> 32:17.640
I didn't want to ruin your clothes.

32:17.640 --> 32:20.880
I usually wash gentlemen's clothes.

32:20.880 --> 32:22.480
Oh, no.

32:22.480 --> 32:23.480
Says the woman.

32:23.480 --> 32:26.720
I want you to be happy.

32:26.720 --> 32:33.120
Toad is worried, but he thinks it can't be so difficult to wash.

32:33.120 --> 32:36.600
Half an hour later, Toad is angry.

32:36.600 --> 32:39.120
The clothes are still dirty.

32:39.120 --> 32:42.000
Suddenly, he hears the barge woman.

32:42.000 --> 32:44.000
She is laughing.

32:44.000 --> 32:46.600
You can't wash.

32:46.600 --> 32:48.800
You aren't a washer woman.

32:48.800 --> 32:50.800
Toad is furious.

32:50.800 --> 32:53.400
You come and barge woman.

32:53.480 --> 32:58.280
I'm Toad, the distinguished Toad.

32:58.280 --> 33:01.080
You mustn't laugh at me.

33:01.080 --> 33:04.320
The woman looks at Toad under his bonnet.

33:04.320 --> 33:06.080
Yes, you are.

33:06.080 --> 33:07.080
She cries.

33:07.080 --> 33:12.160
A horrible Toad in my nice clean barge.

33:12.160 --> 33:19.080
She takes him by the legs and throws him into the water.

33:19.080 --> 33:21.560
It is very cold.

33:21.640 --> 33:23.960
Toad gets out of the water.

33:23.960 --> 33:26.720
He looks at the woman.

33:26.720 --> 33:29.480
She is laughing at him.

33:29.480 --> 33:32.280
Toad wants revenge.

33:32.280 --> 33:34.520
He runs after the barge.

33:34.520 --> 33:38.440
He takes the horse and gallops away.

33:38.440 --> 33:39.440
Stop!

33:39.440 --> 33:40.440
Stop!

33:40.440 --> 33:41.440
Stop!

33:41.440 --> 33:44.120
Shouts the woman.

33:44.120 --> 33:50.000
Toad laughs.

33:50.000 --> 33:57.960
After some miles, Toad and the horse are sleepy and the horse stops to eat some grass.

33:57.960 --> 34:00.080
Toad looks around.

34:00.080 --> 34:04.680
He sees an old, dirty, gypsy caravan.

34:04.680 --> 34:07.600
There is a man sitting next to it.

34:07.600 --> 34:11.080
There is also a fire.

34:11.080 --> 34:16.440
Over the fire is a pot full of stew.

34:16.440 --> 34:23.680
It is very hungry, and the stew smells delicious.

34:23.680 --> 34:26.920
The gypsy asks, do you want to say your horse?

34:26.920 --> 34:29.600
Oh no, replies Toad.

34:29.600 --> 34:34.400
I love my horse, but how much can you pay me?

34:34.400 --> 34:37.600
A shilling a leg replies the gypsy.

34:37.600 --> 34:41.720
A shilling a leg says Toad.

34:41.720 --> 34:45.400
I must work out how much that is in total.

34:45.400 --> 34:52.680
He thinks for a minute, but that only for shillings, I cannot accept that.

34:52.680 --> 34:58.200
Give me six shillings and some breakfast and you can have my horse.

34:58.200 --> 35:04.040
The gypsy agrees and gives Toad six shillings.

35:04.040 --> 35:09.200
Then he gives him an enormous plate of stew.

35:09.200 --> 35:14.440
Toad eats and eats and eats.

35:14.440 --> 35:21.200
After the gypsy gives him directions for the riverbank and Toad says goodbye.

35:21.200 --> 35:24.000
He is happy again.

35:24.000 --> 35:26.120
The sun is shining.

35:26.120 --> 35:31.000
He has money in his pockets and a full stock.

35:31.000 --> 35:35.360
And he is near home.

35:35.360 --> 35:39.000
After some time he sees a car in the distance.

35:39.000 --> 35:40.640
Wonderful!

35:41.640 --> 35:44.840
I can stop the car and ask for a lift.

35:44.840 --> 35:48.720
Then I can return to Toad Hall in a car.

35:48.720 --> 35:54.920
He steps into the road and the car slows down.

35:54.920 --> 36:00.120
But suddenly Toad becomes pale and falls to the ground.

36:00.120 --> 36:07.560
It is the car from outside the red lion and the people in the car are the same people.

36:07.640 --> 36:09.240
Oh no!

36:09.240 --> 36:10.960
Prison again!

36:10.960 --> 36:14.560
Dry bread and water again!

36:14.560 --> 36:16.400
Ha ha ha ha!

36:16.400 --> 36:18.440
What a fool I am!

36:18.440 --> 36:21.640
Tried Toad.

36:21.640 --> 36:26.840
The car stops and two men get out.

36:26.840 --> 36:27.920
Oh dear!

36:27.920 --> 36:30.320
A washer woman in the road.

36:30.320 --> 36:33.360
Let's take her to the village.

36:33.440 --> 36:39.440
They put Toad in the car and continue along the road.

36:39.440 --> 36:44.200
Toad feels brave again because the men do not recognise him.

36:44.200 --> 36:46.560
How do you feel now?

36:46.560 --> 36:48.360
Asks one of the men.

36:48.360 --> 36:49.360
Better!

36:49.360 --> 36:50.920
Thank you sir!

36:50.920 --> 36:51.920
Says Toad.

36:51.920 --> 36:58.280
But maybe if I can sit in the front seat next to the driver I can have some fresh air

36:58.280 --> 37:00.320
on my face.

37:00.320 --> 37:03.600
The sensible says the man.

37:03.600 --> 37:06.960
So Toad gets into the front seat.

37:06.960 --> 37:08.440
Please sir!

37:08.440 --> 37:09.440
Says Toad.

37:09.440 --> 37:12.240
Can I drive the car for a little?

37:12.240 --> 37:15.640
The driver laughs.

37:15.640 --> 37:19.200
You can try madam.

37:19.200 --> 37:24.800
Toad gets into the driver's seat and pretends to listen to the driver's instructions.

37:24.800 --> 37:27.960
At first he drives very carefully.

37:27.960 --> 37:30.560
The two men laugh and applaud.

37:30.560 --> 37:37.040
Oh, just imagine a washer woman driving so well.

37:37.040 --> 37:39.960
Toad goes a little faster.

37:39.960 --> 37:44.120
Then faster and faster.

37:44.120 --> 37:48.800
The men say be careful washer woman.

37:48.800 --> 37:53.200
This annoys Toad and he loses his head.

37:53.200 --> 37:55.240
The washer woman!

37:55.240 --> 37:56.240
He shouts.

37:56.240 --> 38:03.040
I'm Toad the motor car thief the famous the clever the fearless Toad.

38:03.040 --> 38:10.480
The two men jump on Toad and the car goes off the road and finishes up in a pond.

38:10.480 --> 38:16.400
Toad flies through the air and lands on the soft grass of a meadow.

38:16.400 --> 38:20.760
He gets up and starts to run.

38:21.760 --> 38:23.760
He cries.

38:23.760 --> 38:27.680
Toad wins again clever Toad.

38:27.680 --> 38:29.960
He looks behind him.

38:29.960 --> 38:35.240
He sees the driver and two policemen running after him.

38:35.240 --> 38:37.320
What an idiot I am!

38:37.320 --> 38:39.560
He cries while he runs.

38:39.560 --> 38:43.400
How stupid I am!

38:43.400 --> 38:49.160
He runs and runs but they get nearer.

38:49.160 --> 38:51.080
The poor Toad.

38:51.080 --> 38:55.280
He is a fat animal and his legs are short.

38:55.280 --> 38:58.800
Suddenly he falls into water.

38:58.800 --> 39:01.440
He is in the river.

39:01.440 --> 39:07.240
The water carries him along and soon he sees a big hole in the riverbank.

39:07.240 --> 39:14.880
He takes hold and pulls himself out of the water.

39:14.880 --> 39:21.760
He looks into the hole and sees a familiar face brown and small.

39:21.760 --> 39:25.280
It is the water rat.

39:25.280 --> 39:30.960
Toad tries to tell rat about his adventures and about how clever he is.

39:30.960 --> 39:33.360
But rat is very serious.

39:33.360 --> 39:36.320
Toad, you are very silly.

39:36.320 --> 39:41.120
You must try to be sensible and mustn't embarrass your friends.

39:41.120 --> 39:43.520
Toad is very sorry.

39:43.600 --> 39:45.760
You are right, Ratty, he says.

39:45.760 --> 39:48.320
I want to be a good Toad in the future.

39:48.320 --> 39:53.840
Let's have coffee and then I can go to Toad Hall and get some clean clothes.

39:53.840 --> 39:55.200
Go to Toad Hall.

39:55.200 --> 39:56.560
Tries rat.

39:56.560 --> 39:58.000
Don't you know?

39:58.000 --> 40:00.000
Toad becomes pale.

40:00.000 --> 40:02.400
No, what, Ratty?

40:02.400 --> 40:05.520
You don't know about the ferrets and the weasels.

40:05.520 --> 40:07.760
They are living in Toad Hall.

40:07.760 --> 40:10.480
They think you aren't coming back from prison.

40:10.560 --> 40:14.960
They lie in bed half the day and eat your food and drink your drink.

40:14.960 --> 40:17.120
The place is in a mess.

40:17.120 --> 40:19.280
Toad gets up and takes a stick.

40:19.920 --> 40:22.480
It's no good, says Rat.

40:22.480 --> 40:25.200
They've got centuries and are armed.

40:25.200 --> 40:26.640
You must wait.

40:26.640 --> 40:28.720
But Toad doesn't want to wait.

40:29.360 --> 40:32.080
He marches down the road to Toad Hall.

40:33.120 --> 40:35.600
At the front gate there is a ferret.

40:35.680 --> 40:39.600
He shoots at Toad and so Toad runs back to Rat.

40:40.880 --> 40:43.280
Badger and Mole arrive.

40:43.280 --> 40:46.720
We can't attack the house, says Badger.

40:46.720 --> 40:50.480
They're too strong, but there's a tunnel.

40:50.480 --> 40:54.560
It goes from the riverbank to the middle of Toad Hall.

40:54.560 --> 41:00.800
Tomorrow night it's the Chief Weasel's birthday and there's a big party in the dining room.

41:00.800 --> 41:06.240
We can enter secretly and then run into the dining room with our pistols and swords.

41:06.800 --> 41:10.560
Yes, yes, cries Toad happily.

41:11.200 --> 41:15.360
Now it's time to go to bed, says Badger.

41:15.360 --> 41:20.240
We must rest because we've got a lot of work to do tomorrow night.

41:30.880 --> 41:35.600
Chapter 8 The Return of Mr. Toad

41:43.520 --> 41:47.840
The following evening Rat calls everyone into the sitting room

41:47.840 --> 41:50.080
and prepares them for the expedition.

41:51.200 --> 41:56.320
He gives them a belt, a sword, a pair of pistols, a policeman's truncheon,

41:56.320 --> 41:59.600
handcuffs, a flask and a sandwich box.

42:01.040 --> 42:04.960
When they are ready, Badger takes a lantern and says,

42:04.960 --> 42:10.800
Now follow me, Mole first, then Rat and Toad last.

42:10.800 --> 42:13.360
And Toady, don't talk.

42:14.720 --> 42:19.040
Toad wants to be part of the expedition, so he is quiet.

42:20.160 --> 42:25.920
Badger takes them along the river for a little way and then goes into a hole in the riverbank.

42:25.920 --> 42:34.160
Mole and Rat follow silently, but Toad slips and falls into the water with a loud splash.

42:36.560 --> 42:40.320
His friends pull him out, but Badger is very angry.

42:41.840 --> 42:44.240
They continue along the secret tunnel.

42:44.960 --> 42:50.560
It is cold and dark and poor Toad starts to shiver because he is frightened

42:51.200 --> 42:53.920
and also because he is completely wet.

42:54.240 --> 42:59.120
At last, Badger says, We must be under the hall now.

42:59.120 --> 43:01.840
They are at the end of the tunnel.

43:01.840 --> 43:05.840
There is a door and they all push against it.

43:05.840 --> 43:10.640
It opens and they are in the pantry next to the dining room.

43:10.640 --> 43:14.320
The weasels are making a lot of noise.

43:14.320 --> 43:19.120
They hear the chief weasels say, Thank you, thank you.

43:19.120 --> 43:27.360
But before I finish, I would like to say one word about our kind host, Mr. Toad.

43:27.360 --> 43:31.760
Good, modest, honest Toad.

43:31.760 --> 43:36.320
Everybody laughs and Toad is furious.

43:38.160 --> 43:43.920
Badger stands up, takes his stick and says, The time is come, follow me.

43:44.080 --> 43:50.160
They open the door and the four friends run into the dining room.

43:51.280 --> 43:55.360
The weasels and ferrets are terrified and run everywhere in a panic.

43:56.800 --> 44:01.840
The four friends go up and down the room, hitting the animals with their sticks

44:02.560 --> 44:06.880
and the weasels and ferrets try to escape through the windows and up the chimney.

44:08.560 --> 44:11.760
After five minutes, the room is empty.

44:12.720 --> 44:18.320
Now, Toad says Badger, We've got your house back for you.

44:18.320 --> 44:20.960
Now you can get us some food.

44:20.960 --> 44:22.240
I'm hungry.

44:23.280 --> 44:27.280
Toad is a little offended because Badger doesn't tell him,

44:27.280 --> 44:30.560
Well done and you are a great fighter.

44:31.440 --> 44:35.440
But he says nothing and finds some food for them to eat.

44:35.680 --> 44:39.680
The next morning, Toad wakes up late as usual.

44:44.240 --> 44:46.320
He comes down for breakfast.

44:46.320 --> 44:53.600
Rat and Mole are sitting in the garden and Badger is in the armchair, reading the newspaper.

44:53.600 --> 44:59.600
Toad says Badger, You must have a banquet to celebrate your return

44:59.600 --> 45:02.880
and you must write the invitations now.

45:03.760 --> 45:04.960
What?

45:04.960 --> 45:11.200
Cries Toad, I must stay inside and write letters on a lovely morning like this.

45:12.080 --> 45:14.320
But then, Toad has an idea.

45:14.960 --> 45:19.280
But wait, of course, the Badger, I can start immediately.

45:19.840 --> 45:25.920
Toad wants to write about his important part in the fight and also about his many adventures.

45:26.960 --> 45:31.600
He also thinks he can give a speech and sing some songs at the banquet.

45:33.040 --> 45:39.440
He works hard all morning and when a weasel knocks at the door at midday and asks if he can

45:39.440 --> 45:43.440
be of service, Toad tells him to deliver the invitations.

45:45.040 --> 45:49.360
But after lunch, Rat and Badger sit toad in a chair.

45:50.320 --> 45:54.960
Look, Toad says Rat, You must understand.

45:55.680 --> 45:59.920
You can't give a speech or sing songs.

45:59.920 --> 46:02.960
Can't I sing just one little song?

46:02.960 --> 46:04.000
asks Toad.

46:04.960 --> 46:06.960
No, says Rat.

46:06.960 --> 46:14.320
You know that your songs are all boasting and vanity and your speech is a gross exaggeration.

46:15.200 --> 46:17.600
You know you must change.

46:18.160 --> 46:19.120
You're right.

46:19.120 --> 46:24.400
I promise to be a different Toad, but this is a hard world.

46:25.200 --> 46:31.360
That evening when the banquet begins, Toad enters the dining room to meet his guests.

46:31.920 --> 46:37.200
All the animals cheer and congratulate him, but Toad is very humble.

46:38.000 --> 46:44.160
Oh no, he says, Badger, Rat and Mole are the real heroes.

46:45.200 --> 46:51.200
The animals are very puzzled by his behavior and Toad is happy because he feels that everyone

46:51.200 --> 46:53.040
is very interested in him.

46:54.400 --> 47:01.200
At the end of the evening, some animals ask for a speech and a song, but Toad shakes his head.

47:02.240 --> 47:04.880
He is a changed Toad.

47:06.560 --> 47:13.200
After this great adventure, the four animals continue their lives in joy and contentment.

47:14.640 --> 47:19.680
Toad sends a gold chain and lock it with pearls to the jailer's daughter

47:19.680 --> 47:21.760
with a modest and grateful letter.

47:22.720 --> 47:26.320
The train driver also receives thanks and compensation.

47:27.360 --> 47:32.240
And Badger also makes Toad send money to the bard woman for her horse.

47:34.080 --> 47:39.840
Sometimes during the long summer evenings, the friends go for a walk in the wild wood.

47:40.560 --> 47:43.120
The weasels greet them with respect.

47:43.840 --> 47:47.360
Mother weasels call their children point and say,

47:47.360 --> 47:52.960
look, there goes great Mr. Toad, the brave rat and famous Mr. Mole.

47:58.560 --> 48:05.520
But when their children are naughty, they say that the terrible grey Badger is coming to get them.

48:07.360 --> 48:15.840
This is of course not true, because Badger is very fond of children, but it always has an effect.

